trans-unit.source: Encapsulates the HTTP intrinsic object that provides access to session-state values, session-level settings, and lifetime management methods.

The <xref:System.Web.HttpSessionStateWrapper> class derives from the <xref:System.Web.HttpSessionStateBase> class and serves as a wrapper for the <xref:System.Web.SessionState.HttpSessionState> class.
This class exposes the functionality of the <xref:System.Web.SessionState.HttpSessionState> class and exposes the <xref:System.Web.HttpSessionStateBase> type.

The <xref:System.Web.HttpSessionStateBase> class lets you replace the original implementation of the <xref:System.Web.SessionState.HttpSessionState> class in your application with a custom implementation, such as when you perform unit testing outside the ASP.NET pipeline.
